A four-day event bringing music to Southampton has come to a close. The Summer Sessions event ran throughout June until Sunday, with a jam-packed schedule of performers. Acts including the Kaiser Chiefs, Loyle Carner, French band Air and Sophie Ellis-Bextor were in the line-up. Singer Paloma Faith had been due to perform on the Friday, but announced on the day she had to cancel due to exhaustion.Summer Sessions organisers have confirmed on their website they hope to return to the city in 2025.
